            "definition": "Tethysuchia is the largest clade within Crocodylomorpha containing Dyrosaurus phosphaticus (Thomas 1893), Elosuchus cherifiensis (Lavocat 1955), and Pholidosaurus schaumburgensis Meyer, 1841, but not Thalattosuchus superciliosus (Blainville 1853), Goniopholis crassidens Owen 1841, Anteophthalmosuchus hooleyi Salisbury and Naish 2011, or Crocodylus niloticus (Laurenti 1768).",
